<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Conversions Api on Simo Ahava's blog</title><link>https://www.simoahava.com/amp/tags/conversions-api/</link><description>Recent content in Conversions Api on Simo Ahava's blog</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 19 Mar 2021 07:42:34 +0200</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.simoahava.com/amp/tags/conversions-api/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Facebook Conversions API Using GA4 Web Tags And A GTM Server</title><link>https://www.simoahava.com/amp/analytics/facebook-conversions-api-gtm-server-side-tagging/</link><pubDate>Fri, 19 Mar 2021 07:42:34 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://www.simoahava.com/amp/analytics/facebook-conversions-api-gtm-server-side-tagging/</guid><description>&lt;p>Facebook has now &lt;strong>officially&lt;/strong> released their &lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/business/help/702509907046774">&lt;strong>Conversions API tag template&lt;/strong>&lt;/a> for &lt;a href="https://www.simoahava.com/amp/analytics/server-side-tagging-google-tag-manager/">server-side tagging in Google Tag Manager&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>With this tag template, you can create a server-side tag that fires with any &lt;a href="https://www.simoahava.com/amp/analytics/server-side-tagging-google-tag-manager/#clients-and-tags">Client&lt;/a> designed to parse requests into a &lt;a href="https://www.simoahava.com/amp/analytics/server-side-tagging-google-tag-manager/#event-model">unified event model&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>


 &lt;a href="https://www.simoahava.com/amp/images/2021/03/facebook-conversions-api-tag.jpg" title="Facebook Conversions API Tag">
 
 &lt;amp-img src="https://www.simoahava.com/amp/images/2021/03/facebook-conversions-api-tag.jpg" layout="responsive" alt="Facebook Conversions API Tag" height="1192" width="1802">&lt;/amp-img>
 
 &lt;/a>
 

&lt;p>One such Client already exists, and every single Server container has it built-in: the &lt;strong>GA4 Client&lt;/strong>.&lt;/p>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>If you haven&amp;rsquo;t yet deployed a Server container, check out &lt;a href="https://youtu.be/6OGbOh216mU">this video walkthrough&lt;/a> for more details on how to do it.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>